               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430612-name-1181" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430612-name-1181" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430612-name-1181" type="surname" value="SUTTON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430612-name-1181" type="given" value="SAMUEL THOMAS"></interp>SAMUEL THOMAS SUTTON</persName>
                  </hi>. On Sunday, the 4th of June, I was passing down Shadwell—the prisoner followed me—I felt my pocket move—I turned, and collared the prisoner—he had my handkerchief in his right hand, and was putting it into his pocket—directly I took him, his friends got up, and get him from me—he went round the corner—the policeman seized him, and he was taken—I had laid hold of him—my handkerchief was hardly out of my pocket—he begged of me to let him go—he put it up to his left-breast pocket—I pulled it from his hand.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner.</hi> I had no pocket, I could not put it in.</p>
               <p>
